======================================================================
PART 6: freed(v) vs freed(w) adjacency in restricted(v) graph
======================================================================
If v is bad, freed(v) ISOLATED from remaining-dom including freed(w)\v
So freed(v) NOT adj to freed(w)\v in restricted(v).
Question: Can this hold for BOTH v and w simultaneously?

